My Meme

I made a new version of the â€œAwkward Monkey Puppetâ€ meme to accurately display how I often feel after starting a new semester â€¦ should have studied that!

library(magick)

# Bottom row images
monkey1 <- image_read(path = "monkey1.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400)
 
monkey2 <- image_read(path = "monkey2.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400)
  
monkey_combined <- image_append(c(monkey1, monkey2))

# Top row text
meme_text <- image_blank(width = 800, height = 300, color = "#F1D575") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me when the lecturer mentions \ncontent from pre-requisite courses",
                 color = "gray", size = 35, font = "Courier New", gravity = "center")

# Creating the meme
final_meme <- c(meme_text, monkey_combined) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) 

final_meme

# Saving the meme
image_write(final_meme, "Meme.png")

My animated GIF

This GIF is close to home for me as I often find myself waiting for Christmas day, then spend all of boxing day paying off the food I ate - what better way to show this than with cats!

library(magick)

# creating individual frames

dec_23 <- image_read(path = "grumpy_cat.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "December 23", size = 40, color = "white", boxcolor = "#3014e3", location = "+10+10")

dec_24 <- image_read(path = "normal_cat.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "December 24", size = 40, color = "white", boxcolor = "#7e14c9", location = "+10+10")

dec_25 <- image_read(path = "xmas_cat.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Christmas Day!", size = 40, color = "white", boxcolor = "#d91660", location = "+10+10")

boxing_day <- image_read(path = "sleepy_cat.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "...Boxing day",size = 80, color = "white", boxcolor = "#e075bb", gravity = "north")

# Ordering, animating

frames <- c(dec_23, dec_24, dec_25, boxing_day)
my_animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 0.5) 

my_animation

# Saving the animation

image_write(my_animation, "my_animation.gif")
